HEADWORD: Carousal
<hw>Ca*rous"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Carouse</er>, but also cf. F. <ets>carrousel</ets> tilt.]</ety>
<def>A jovial feast or festival; a drunken revel; a carouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The swains were preparing for a <qex>carousal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Banquet; revel; orgie; carouse. See
<er>Feast</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 220 --></p>

<p><ent>Carouse</ent>⟦br⟧
